An applicant for the approval of a dry lease-in of an aircraft registered in a third country shall demonstrate to the competent authority that: Select 3
1. an operational need has been identified that cannot be satisfied through leasing an aircraft registered in the EU;
2. the duration of the dry lease-in does not exceed seven months in any 12 consecutive month period; 
3. compliance with the applicable requirements of EASA Regulations is ensured.
4. the safety standards of the lessor are equivalent to EASA
5. the lessor holds an AOC from an ICAO contracting state

Which of the following statements correctly describes what an operator must demonstrate before the issue of an Air Operators Certificate (AOC)?

(i) Organisation, method of control and supervision of flight operations;
(ii) Training programmes;
(iii) Maintenance arrangements.
